article.headline: Smith leads Bucs with 26
article.linkText: East Tennessee State holds off Fresno State
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Tim Smith scored 26 points and dished out five assists as East Tennessee State held off Fresno State for a 66-62 nonconference victory Saturday. Zakee Wadood and Jerald Fields scored 13 points apiece and combined for 23 rebounds for ETSU. Fresno State's Shantay Legans and Marcus West also scored 13 points each. Legans added 10 assists. ETSU bolted to a quick 10-0 lead and led 36-25 at halftime. Fresno State trailed 43-32 with 16:30 remaining before rallying to force two ties. But the hosts were unable to go ahead. Leading 64-62 with 13.5 seconds left, ETSU twice missed the front end of one-and-ones but both times collected the offensive rebound. The Bulldogs were forced to foul and Smith's two free throws with 7 seconds left sealed the victory. ETSU improved to 23-4 overall with its 15th consecutive victory. Fresno State dropped to 12-12.
